	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here's how to get the axe:<BR>
<BR>
Go to Kaladim (the dwarf city) and find Beno in the Warrior's Guild.  Ask him &quot;What important stormguard matter?&quot; and he will give you a letter and tell you about the Eye of Stormhammer.  Take the letter to the Jail Clerk in Highpass Keep to get the Cracked Emerald (it's a container).  Now go to Misty Thicket.  Find the southernmost tower at The Wall and on the top of it is a halfling rogue named Bronin.  Ask him &quot;What small favor?&quot; (NOTE:  unless you have good faction, you'll need to make a halfling rogue for this part to work.  Just make one and ask him the question then sign back on as your main char).  Asking this will make a froglok named Slaythe appear near the orc camp (northwest corner of misty).  Slaythe will kill you if you solo at 25, so you may need a group if your below 26.  He's a level 22 mob I believe.  Anyway, get his leg from the corpse and give it to Bronin to get a key.  Give the key to the bank clerk in Highpass Keep to get an emerald shard.  Put the shard into the cracked emerald container.  Now travel to North Qeynos.  Find Crow's bar and look for the back room (it has a painting in it that you can walk through).  Sit in this back room until Faldor Hendrys spawns (can take 2 hours sometimes, usually less).  Kill Faldor (he's much easier than Slaythe, about level 21) to get the second emerald shard.  Put it in the cracked emerald container with the first one and click &quot;combine&quot;.  Now take the completed Eye of Stormhammer and give it to Beno back at the warrior's guild in Kaladim to get 8-10 plat and the Avenger Battle Axe.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
